				<sender type="str">w-nws.webmaster@noaa.gov</sender>
				<senderName type="str">NWS Paducah KY</senderName>
				<headline type="str">High Wind Warning issued March 15 at 12:59PM CDT until March 15 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
				<description type="str">* WHAT...South winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 60 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of southern Illinois, southwest Indiana, western
Kentucky, and southeast Missouri.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CDT this evening.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.</description>
				<instruction type="str">Remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and
avoid windows. Watch for falling debris and tree limbs. Use caution
if you must drive.</instruction>
